"As of Sunday [28 Feb 2021], health authorities in Guinea had vaccinated more than 1100 people against Ebola, Mike Ryan, the WHO's top emergencies official, told a media briefing.

"We have identified approximately 500 contacts and 99% of them are currently tracked and followed," he said.]

- Sun 28 Feb 2021.
[WHO/AFRO, Weekly Bulletin on Outbreaks and Other Emergencies; abridged, edited]
https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/339897/OEW09-2228022021.pdf

Week 9: 22-28 Feb 2021; data as reported by: 28 Feb 2021
Ebola virus disease Guinea CFR 41.2%
------------------------------------
Event description
The outbreak of Ebola virus disease (EVD) declared in Guinea on 14 Feb 2021 continues, with one new confirmed case reported in Nzerekore on 28 Feb 2021, in a community death (unknown contact). A safe and dignified burial was performed. A suspected patient from Bayle is still waiting for results. As of 28 Feb 2021, there is a total of 17 cases (13 confirmed and 4 probable) and seven deaths (case fatality ratio 41.2%). Currently, only one health district is active (reporting at least one confirmed cases) and 6 health districts are on alert (have at least one contact) out of 38. A total of 495 (99%) contacts out of 498 are being followed up. There is an ongoing search for three contacts who are lost to follow-up.

Ebola virus disease Democratic Republic of the Congo CFR 50.0%
--------------------------------------------------------------
Event description
The Ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreak announced on 7 Feb 2021 in Butembo continues. However, there were no new confirmed cases on 27 Feb 2021, marking 5 days since the last confirmed case was reported, in Masoya health area, Biena Health Zone. As of 27 Feb 2021, there are 8 [now 11] confirmed cases, with 4 deaths (case fatality ratio 50.0%). In the past 21 days, 8 new cases have been confirmed, 3 each in Biena, Katwa, and Musienene health zones, spread among 5 health areas. No new contacts were listed on 27 Feb 2021. As of 27 Feb 2021, a total of 785 contacts have been listed, of whom 701 (89.3%) have been followed-up. A total of 84 have not been followed-up; among these, 27 have never been seen, 37 are lost to follow-up, 18 have not been seen in the past 24 hours and two are displaced. A total of 216 new alerts were reported on 27 Feb 2021, including 11 deaths, from 7 health zones. Of the 260 alerts to date, 217 have been investigated, with 67 (30.8%) validated and 63 (94%) have provided samples.

