[3] Confronting Ebola
Date: Tue 2 Mar 2021 12:13 PST
Source: France24 [abridged, edited]
https://www.france24.com/en/tv-shows/perspective/20210302-ebola-can-be-tackled-in-africa-even-amid-covid-19-expert-says


Ebola can be tackled in Africa even amid COVID-19, expert says
--------------------------------------------------------------
Our guest is Paulin Basinga, Director of Health, Africa for the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation. He says the "resilience" of people and health programmes in place across Africa mean both Ebola and the coronavirus can and will be tackled. Basinga spoke to us as Guinea is dealing with a new outbreak of Ebola which has caused at least 6 deaths and as many other African countries are still dealing with COVID-19. He says the experience of tackling a variety of health issues means the continent has an advantage in knowing how to treat and contain such problems.

Basinga also welcomed the arrival of the 1st COVID-19 vaccines in Africa but said more solidarity from richer nations is needed.

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall

[This report includes a 10-minute video interview with Paulin Basinga in Seattle (Washington, USA) - Mod.LK]
